WorkItem.Description:
I found the following bug: if the description of a node/edge is in the same xml line, alternate data information is ignored. This is due to the following code
 
                    // read data
                    while (subReader.Read())
                    {
                        if (reader.NodeType == XmlNodeType.Element &&
                            reader.Name == "data" &&
                            reader.NamespaceURI == this.graphMLNamespace)
                            ReadDelegateCompiler.VertexAttributesReader(subReader, this.graphMLNamespace, vertex);
                    }
 
Since the VertexAttributesReader advances also the reader, when there is no intermediate node, the are two consecutive reads and one is lost.
 
The following code change in the loop corrects the situation:
 
                    // read data
                    subReader.Read();  
                    while (!subReader.EOF)  //changed guard
                    {
                        if (reader.NodeType == XmlNodeType.Element &&
                            reader.Name == "data" &&
                            reader.NamespaceURI == this.graphMLNamespace)
                        {
                            ReadDelegateCompiler.VertexAttributesReader(subReader, this.graphMLNamespace, vertex);
                        }
                        else
                            subReader.Read();  //also advance here
                    }
